Package: ouija
Title: Incorporating prior knowledge in single-cell trajectory learning using
    Bayesian nonlinear factor analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Kieran", "Campbell", email = "kieranc@well.ox.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Ouija learns trajectories or 'pseudotimes' from single-cell RNA-seq data. Using Bayesian 
  nonlinear factor analysis biological knowledge of gene expression across pseudotime can be
  encoded as informative priors in the model.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.2.3)
License: MIT
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    ggplot2,
    rstan,
    MCMCglmm,
    coda,
    cowplot,
    reshape2,
    viridis,
    dplyr,
    matrixStats
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
